The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for the estimation of weights in combinatorial optimization problems, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with discrete optimization problems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of linear programming and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of relaxation techniques and warmstarting, which are common in the field of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
